com.example.moelkky
Class Player

java.lang.Object
  com.example.moelkky.Player

public class Player
extends java.lang.Object

Stores information of single player. Player stores name, last three throws and total score, also calculates if player drops due three misses, accessed with getters and setters.

Author:
Joakim

inGame

public boolean inGame()
Tells if user is still in game. Method checks if user is still in game by making sure, that he has not made 3 misses in a row (misscounter < 3)

Returns:
boolean depending if player is still in game
See Also:
misscounter

newThrow

public boolean newThrow(int result)
Updates object with result of last throw made. Method updates score and three last throws with given result Integer It also checks if player goes over 50 points, and if so, sets score to 25 Returns false by default, true if player wins with the throw made

Parameters:
Integer - value of last throw made (0-12)
Returns:
true if player wins the game with the throw, false if not
See Also:
misscounter, score
